from sharon sharon m gartenberg subject from srebrenica doctoring in hell srebrenica doctor recount town living hell by laura pitter tuzla bosnium reuter neret mujanovic wa a pathologist when he trek through the mountain to the besiege muslim town of srebrenica last august but after treat mangle victim of bosnium bloody war he consider himself a surgeon now i a surgeon with great experience although i have no license to practice but if i operate on a person and he life normally that the greatest license a surgeon could have evacuated by the thi week to hi home town of tuzla the muslim physician give an eyewitnes medical assessment of the horror of the year-long serb siege of srebrenica and the suffer of the thousand trap there i live through hell together with the person of srebrenica all those who live through thi be the greatest hero that humanity can produce he tell reporter mujanovic have practice for two month a an assistant at a local hospital in tuzla but before go to srebrenica he have never perform a surgical operation on hi own now he say he ha perform major surgery time rely on book for guidance amputate arm and leg time usually without anesthetic deliver baby and perform fmy cesarean section he work day sleep in the hospital for the first week after hi arrival last aug and treat patient he arrive after make the trek over mountain on foot from tuzla mile northwest of srebrenica about other person carry in supply and soldier guide and protect him through guerrilla terrain he say hi worst memory wa of day ago when seven serb shell land within one minute in an area half the size of a football field kill person immediately and wound half of the dead be woman and child the person have come out for a rare day of sunshine and the child be play soccer there wa no warn the blood flow like a river in the street he say there be piece of woman all around and you could not piece them together one woman hold her two child in her hand wa lie with them on the grind dead they have no head before mujanovic arrive with hi supply condition be deplorable he say many death could have be prevent have the hospital have surgical tool facility and medicine the six general practitioner who have be operate before he arrive have even le surgical experience than he do they do know the basic principle for amputate limb once he arrive the situation improve he say but by mid-september he have run out of supply bandage be wash and boil five time sometime they be fall apart in my hand he say doctor have no anesthetic and could not give patient alcohol to numb the pain because it increase bleed person be completely consciou during amputation and stomach operation he say blood transfusion be impossible because they have no facility to test blood type i felt destroy psychologically mujanovic say the situation improve after dec when a convoy arrive from the belgian medical group medecin san frontiere but mujanovic say the military predicament worsen in mid-december after bosnian serb begin a major offensive in the region every day we have air strike and shell then the hunger set in between mid-december and mid-march when plane begin air drop food between and person be die every day from complication associate with malnutrition he say i know for sure that the air drop operation save the person from massive death by hunger and starvation he say according to mujanovic around person die in srebrenica of them child during a year of siege mujanovic plan to return to srebrenica in three week after visit hi wife who be ill in tuzla they say i a hero he say there be thousand of person stand at the side of the road cry and wave when i leave and i cry too sharon machli gartenberg framingham ma usa e-mail sharon 